body:
Hi, I need to convert the "workbook.xlsx" previously read from a stream, to csv format to be able to write it in another stream. Currently what I have is the following

 ```
 async transformExcelToCsvStream(entryStream, fileName, finalStream){
    const workbook = new Exceljs.Workbook()
    await workbook.xlsx.read(entryStream)
    await workbook.csv.write(finalStream,{ sheetName: `${fileName}.csv` })
  };
 ```

When checking the write result I find an empty .csv file.

comments.body:
@JonatanAlcaraz did you find a solution?

I'm having a similar issue when writing a XLSX with a stream... the result file is empty despite committing all rows, sheets and the workbook.

EDIT: I used this fix at the end https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/pull/2558 and it works

hi @sneko, I had to create this kind of frankenstein to make it work for me, if there is a "better" way to do it I would like to know it, I hope it helps you:


```
  async transformExcelToCsvStream(xlsxStream) {
    const workbook = new Exceljs.Workbook();
    const csvWriter = format({ headers: true }); //import { format } from "fast-csv";
    const passThroughStream = new PassThrough();
    csvWriter.pipe(passThroughStream);
    await workbook.xlsx.read(xlsxStream).then((wb) => {
      const sheet = wb.getWorksheet("Sheet1");
      sheet.eachRow((row) => {
        csvWriter.write(row.values);
      });
      csvWriter.end();
    });
    return passThroughStream;
  }
```

the `xlsxStream` parameter is a file download made with axios with property `responseType = "stream"`.
